        Field description: Free text fields that allows the user to input the details of the request or the information. This field will be mapped against the tag 45D of a MT759 message. Only upto 8 sequences allowed(i.e. 8/8). This field allows to input a maximum of 1200 lines of 65 characters(Z character set).       • getAccrualParam

        public TField getAccrualParam()
        Returns the AccrualParam

        Field description: This field will hold a valid ID of EB.ACCRUAL.PARAM for the commission and accrual calculations. Based on the definition of this field a contract can be configured to do the following, Include first day of the interest period and exclude the last of the interest period Exclude the first day of the interest period and include the last of the interest period. Include both first (only value date) and last day of accrual period. Adjust the principal increase and decrease effective dates for interest calculation and accrual calculation purposes. By default the field shall hold null in which case the system shall include first day of the interest period and exclude the last of the interest period. This would be a NOCHANGE field after authorization.

      • getAdviceReqd

        public TField getAdviceReqd()
        Returns the AdviceReqd

        Field description: Allows user to decide whether they wish to produce any advices associated with this deal. This field allows the user to suppress any advices that would otherwise be produced over the lifetime of the deal. If this field is set to 'NO' then no advices will be produced. If it is set to 'YES' then a subset of the following advices will be produced in association with the deal during its lifetime. 1 Confirmation of Deal 2 Amendment of Deal 3 Cancellation of Deal 4 Charge confirmations Contract confirmation will be produced only on initial input of the contract and cancellation confirmations only when a contract is reversed. Contract amendment confirmations will be produced whenever the contract principal is amended, i.e. when a principal increase or decrease is entered on the deal. It is important to note that this advice is produced when the amendment is made and not on the value date of the actual movement. Therefore, if a second principal movement is entered before the first has reached its value date both movements will appear on the confirmation. Similarly, whenever the maturity date is amended an amendment confirmation will be produced. Charge advices will be produced whenever charges are debited, i.e. on the charge value date. Validation Rules: Input of 'YES' or 'NO' only. (Defaults to 'YES') Only input 'YES' or 'NO' allowed.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The AdviceReqd

      • getCapitalizeDate

        public TField getCapitalizeDate()
        Returns the CapitalizeDate

        Field description: CAPITALIZE.DATE In the case of frequency based scheduling (End type), if the maturity date falls within the running commission schedule, the Deal will be kept "LIVE" past the maturity date till the end of the commission schedule. The commission will be booked at the end of the schedule. This field opens up to enable booking of commission on a day prior to the end date of the running commission schedule, but after the maturity date. Validation Rules: Can be any date past the Maturity date but less than the date in CSN.FREQUENCY.

        Field description: CSN.FREQUENCY This denotes the frequency in which the commission is cycled for capitalization.         Parameters:

        TField - The CsnFrequency

      • getCsnPaymentType

        public TField getCsnPaymentType()
        Returns the CsnPaymentType

        Field description: At contract level the commission amount payable or receivable can be set to be levied at the beginning (BEGIN) of the commission period or the end (END) of the commission period. The commission period is defined by the start of the contract and the end of the contract with optional interim dates specified by the user. If commission is defined then there must be either a schedule for the start date (for BEGIN contracts) or at maturity (for END contracts). Where it is set to END: Accruals are passed to a P/L category according to the cycling frequency and the customer is debited (or credited according to deal type) at the end of the period. For the bank the effect of the P/L is built up over the life of the contract rather than one lump payment at the end. Where it is set to BEGIN: Accruals are passed to a P/L category according to the cycling frequency and the customer is debited (or credited according to deal type) at the start of the period. This amount is then left in an advance P/L account and then dripped through to the real P/L. This gives the same effect of the P/L build up over the life of the contract as the END method. Validation Rules: BEGIN - payment in advance END - payment in arrears Default is END

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The CsnPaymentType

      • getCsnRate

        public TField getCsnRate()
        Returns the CsnRate

        Field description: This defines the base commission rate that will be used to calculate the commission payable/receivable based on the Amount (inclusive of any forward increases/decreases) and the INTEREST.BASIS field used. This rate may be adjusted by use of the CSN.SPREAD, which can be a positive or negative value, and the real rate to be apllied is then stored in CURRENT.RATE. Validation Rules: Standard Rate format

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The CsnRate

      • getDealSubType

        public TField getDealSubType()
        Returns the DealSubType

        Field description: This field is used to sub divide the CONTRACT.TYPE. This field is used to sub-divide each CONTRACT.TYPE into smaller groups. A Deal Sub Type entered here must have been entered on the MD.PARAMETER record for the company in a position corresponding to the CONTRACT.TYPE entered above. It has no direct bearing on the processing of the deal other than defining the range of allowable categories for the CATEGORY field. It does this through the MD.PARAMETER record. Each Deal Sub Type entered on the MD.PARAMETER is entered with a corresponding range of category codes. This range is used in defining the upper and lower limits for the category code field.       • getInvStatus

        public TField getInvStatus()
        Returns the InvStatus

        Field description: Accepts any of PROCESS, EXECUTE or CANCEL. Input allowed only for authorized MD records. The invocation is done two stages. First is the PROCESS stage, where the user can input the invocation details but no accounting entries/limit are raised. When the invocation is in PROCESS stage, the user can either EXECUTE the invocation or CANCEL it. When option EXECUTE is chosen, accounting entries/limit are raised. If CANCEL option is chosen, the invocation fields are cleared. Again no accounting entries/limit are passed. Validation Rules: Invocation related fields open up only if this holds either PROCESS or EXECUTE. The status can only be PROCESS if the previous value is NULL. The status can only be EXECUTE or CANCEL only if the previous value is PROCESS.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The InvStatus

      • getIssueCustomer

        public TField getIssueCustomer()
        Returns the IssueCustomer

        Field description: MD.DEAL allows the participation by other parties in deals, usually on the Issuance of Guarantees for larger amounts. There would typically be a main deal which details the Guarantee issued, the parties who are participating and the commission rates and dates. Secondary deals relating to the Participation taken by the other parties will be recorded in their name with a share of the commission payable to them. In accounting terms this deal is same as a Guarantee Received with the exception that there are commissions to be paid. The Customer entered here is used to identify the client of the main deal. It is not permitted to enter data in this field and the PARTICIPANT or AMT.PARTICIPATE fields at the same time. Validation Rules: Must be a valid CUSTOMER record Cannot be used together with PARTICIPANT or AMT.PARTICIPATE

        Parameters:
        Returns:

      • getLimitAmount

        public TField getLimitAmount()
        Returns the LimitAmount

        Field description: This is the amount used in the call to limits. The principal amount used for the purposes of limits will be the highest value of the contract either today or in the future taking into account all principal movements. For example consider the following contingent asset contract: 2 CURRENCY USD 4 PRINCIPAL 1,000,000 6 VALUE.DATE 01/01/93 7 MATURITY.DATE 01/04/93 13.1 PRIN.MOVEMENT - 200,000 14.1 MOVEMENT DATE 15/01.93 13.2 PRIN.MOVEMENT 500,000 14.2 MOVEMENT.DATE 01/02/93 13.3 PRIN.MOVEMENT - 100,000 14.3 MOVEMENT.DATE 01/03/93 In this case the principal amount passed to limits would be 1,300,000 as this is the highest value of the principal throughout the contract life. Hence the LIMIT.AMOUNT field would contain 1,300,000. This field will only be updated if LIMIT.UPD.REQD is 'YES'. Validation Rules: Internally generated field. No input allowed.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The LimitAmount

      • getLimitReference

        public TField getLimitReference()
        Returns the LimitReference

        Field description: Identifies the LIMIT REFERENCE number to be checked for Limit control. If LIMIT.UPD.REQD is 'NO' then this field will be a no- input field and limits will not be called. See help text for field LIMIT UPD REQD as to how that field can be set up. If input is allowed and no input is made in this field the Limits System will provide a default according to the LIMIT.PARAMETER.FILE. It will look for the PRODUCT.NO defined under the MD.DEAL.application. The credit line number generated will be NNNN-01 where NNNN is the ID of the Limit Reference record described above. Validation Rules: 3 to 10 characters for a LIMIT REFERENCE code. Input only allowed if LIMIT.UPD.REQD field is equal to 'YES' otherwise no input. (Optional Input, Default value seel details below) Must be a valid reference on the LIMIT Reference table. If no Limit exists for the counterparty a corresponding error message will be displayed by the system with an override facility. If the transaction amount exceeds the availability amount of the Limit, a corresponding error message will be displayed with an override facility. An override is required if the deal VALUE.DATE is before the limit start date. An override is required if the line expires prior to the deal final maturity date.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The LimitReference

      • getLimitUpdReqd

        public TField getLimitUpdReqd()
        Returns the LimitUpdReqd

        Field description: Indicates whether limits are to be updated or not. The interface to limits can be controlled both at the contract and parameter level. At the module parameter level fields are provided to control the use of limits with contingent and memorandum contract types. Via these fields the user can specify if the interface to limits is mandatory, optional or not allowed for these products. The fields used on MD.PARAMETER that do this are: CONT.LIMIT.LINK Can be Mandatory, Optional or Noinput. MEMO.LIMIT.LINK Can be Mandatory, Optional or Noinput. CL.LIMIT.LINK Can be Mandatory, Optional or Noinput. ML.LIMIT.LINK Can be Mandatory, Optional or Noinput. If this field is set to YES then limit processing will be perfomed and the limit type define in LIMIT.PARAMETER will be used. If set to No then no processing is done. Validation Rules: Input must either be 'YES' or 'NO' Default of No is used when limits are set to Noinput in MD.PARAMETER

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The LimitUpdReqd

      • getLiquidationMode

        public TField getLiquidationMode()
        Returns the LiquidationMode

        Field description: This field identifies the manner in which overdue payments are handled. The default for all contracts is AUTOMATIC. There are three options available: AUTOMATIC - will liquidate across the charge/commission account on the contract SEMI AUTOMATIC - will liquidate the charge/commission to the account only if sufficient balance is available. Else, PD will be written MANUAL - will create a PD contract irrespective of availability of funds Only the charges and commissions taken in the deal are reckoned for this purpose. If PD product is not defined for the current company, the only allowed value is AUTOMATIC. Prior to inputting MANUAL or SEMI AUTOMATIC, a Parameter for MD has to be defined in PD.PARAMETER

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The LiquidationMode

      • getMaturityDate

        public TField getMaturityDate()
        Returns the MaturityDate

        Field description: This field represents either the final maturity date of the deal or the number of days notice before maturity.

        If not defined, maturity date will be calculated from ADVICE.EXPIRY.DATE + EXPIRY.DAYS defined in MD.PARAMETER. Validation Rules:

        Standard date format or 1 - 3 numeric characters.

        An override will be required if the date as defined on the HOLIDAY table is a non working day.

        The date must be greater than the VALUE.DATE defined above.

        An override will be required if the field is changed from a notice to a fixed maturity date and the appropriate number of days' notice has not been given.

        If the MATURITY.DATE has been entered in a Date format then any MOVEMENT.DATEs entered below cannot be after the Maturity Date.

        If the MATURITY.DATE has been entered in a DATE format then any CHARGE.DATEs entered below cannot be after the MATURITY.DATE.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The MaturityDate

REIMBURS - Request related to a reimbursement ix.REQAMEND - Request to amend an undertaking x. REQFINAN - Financing request xi. ISSUANCE, REQISSUE, REQAMEND, or ISSAMEND then field MT759.FORM.OF.UNDK must contain UNDK ii. TRANSFER then field MT759.FORM.OF.UNDK must contain DGAR, STBY, or UNDK

        Field description: Free text fields that allows the user to input the details of the request or the information. This field will be mapped against the tag 45D of a MT759 message. Format : 150*65z ( of 8 sequences) Accept Z (Alphanumeric) characters System auto populates 'tag 27 - Sequence of Total' based on the number of MT759 messages generated. Only upto 8 sequences allowed(i.e. 8/8). This field allows to input a maximum of 1200 lines of 65 characters(Z character set). For each of the 150 lines, T24 generates multiple MT759 messages and a maximum of upto 8/8 sequence of messages can generated. Mandatory field for a MT759 message. Validation Rules: The number of lines in this field cannot exceed 1200.

      • getOnlineMat

        public TField getOnlineMat()
        Returns the OnlineMat

        Field description: Input of YES in this field shall ensure that the maturity of the Guarantee Deal is done Online. This is an input field only if the EVENTS.PROCESSING is set as ONLINE. The Maturity would be treated as TODAY. When set Online maturity, the commission accounting entries, Limit reinstatement, Release of Cash Margin are all done online along with liquidation of the Contract. Where the commission is Begin type and Manual and if the Deal were not in its last schedule, the User needs to delete all the future schedules. The accounting entries would however be passed for the entire schedule amount. Where the commission is End type and Manual and if the Deal were not in its last schedule, the User needs to delete all the future schedules and the CSN.DATE has to be input with Current date. The accounting entries would however be passed only for the amount accrued till date. Thus commission accounting entries passed for the Begin type would always be for the entire current schedule and that of the End type would always be for the Accrued amount. When the Commission is set as a frequency, the system would set the CAPITALIZE.DATE as TODAY and the entries would be passed accordingly. Validation Rules: When set to Online maturity the Deal shall not have any Principal movements scheduled. When set to Online maturity the Deal shall not have any Charges scheduled for a future date. When set to Online maturity the Deal shall not have Invocation set to Process, Execute or Cancel. When set to Online maturity the Deal shall not have its Overdue status relating to PD. Online Maturity shall not take place when the contract is linked to Syndicated Loans. Online Maturity shall not take place where the contract is linked to LC, but Drawings under the same are yet to be done. Online Maturity shall not be permitted for any Forward Deals. This field shall accept either YES or NULL.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The OnlineMat

      • getPrincipalAmount

        public TField getPrincipalAmount()
        Returns the PrincipalAmount

        Field description: The principal amount of the deal. This field contains the principal amount of the deal in the currency defined in the CURRENCY field. In order to facilitate the entry of the amount an input feature has been provided which allows for the suppression of trailing zeros. In English language text this is accomplished by using a 'T' to indicate the thousands and an 'M' to indicate the millions. Other languages will require the provision of translation values. e.g. Input Value 1T 1000 2M 2000 000 Validation Rules: 1 - 14 numeric characters plus a decimal point and commas. (Mandatory Input) This field cannot be negative. The decision as to whether the deal represents an asset or liability depends on the value of the CONTRACT.TYPE field entered below. Once the deal has been authorised this field cannot be changed. Any changes to the Principal should be entered using the PRIN.MOVEMENT and MOVEMENT.DATE fields below. This field will then be updated during the end of day of the MOVEMENT.DATE.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The PrincipalAmount

      • getProcessAtSod

        public TField getProcessAtSod()
        Returns the ProcessAtSod

        Field description: This field decides whether the commission and charge is to be processed at SOD or EOD of the scheduled date. The value gets defaulted from the parameter table. However, the user can amend the defaulted value. Acceptable values are YES, NO and None. If yes, then the processing will take place during SOD and if no or none, then the processing will take place during EOD of the scheduled date. Validation Rules: Acceptable values are Yes, No and None The value in this field is changeable during the life of the contract.

      • getSplitCommission

        public TField getSplitCommission()
        Returns the SplitCommission

        Field description: SPLIT.COMMISSION If this field is set to YES, the calculated commission will be split into two parts, one proportionate to the leader's share in the Deal that is reflected in the P&L and the other will be credited to the Internal account as specified in the MD.PARAMETER (Field PART.CSN.ACC). If set to NO, the entire commission, including that relating to the Participants will move into the P&L. If set to NULL, the flow would be that of NO. Validation Rules: Valid input YES or NO.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The SplitCommission

      • getStatus

        public TField getStatus()
        Returns the Status

        Field description: This field indicates the status of the contract. It is an internal field and input here is automatically generated by the system. Having a status defined for each contract will facilitate the production of end of Day reports. The following values have been defined:- 1) FWD = forward value 2) CUR = current 3) REV = reversed 4) LIQ = deal has reached maturity date 5) EXP status of the contract from Advice Expiry date to Maturity Date. Validation Rules:

        System maintained field.

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The Status

        public void insertMt759Narrative(TField param, int pos)
        Insert the specified Mt759Narrative to the specified position in the collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Free text fields that allows the user to input the details of the request or the information. This field will be mapped against the tag 45D of a MT759 message. Format : 150*65z ( of 8 sequences) Accept Z (Alphanumeric) characters System auto populates 'tag 27 - Sequence of Total' based on the number of MT759 messages generated. Only upto 8 sequences allowed(i.e. 8/8). This field allows to input a maximum of 1200 lines of 65 characters(Z character set). For each of the 150 lines, T24 generates multiple MT759 messages and a maximum of upto 8/8 sequence of messages can generated. Mandatory field for a MT759 message. Validation Rules: The number of lines in this field cannot exceed 1200.

      • setAccrualParam

        public void setAccrualParam(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for AccrualParam
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field will hold a valid ID of EB.ACCRUAL.PARAM for the commission and accrual calculations. Based on the definition of this field a contract can be configured to do the following, Include first day of the interest period and exclude the last of the interest period Exclude the first day of the interest period and include the last of the interest period. Include both first (only value date) and last day of accrual period. Adjust the principal increase and decrease effective dates for interest calculation and accrual calculation purposes. By default the field shall hold null in which case the system shall include first day of the interest period and exclude the last of the interest period. This would be a NOCHANGE field after authorization.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setAccrualParam

        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field will hold a valid ID of EB.ACCRUAL.PARAM for the commission and accrual calculations. Based on the definition of this field a contract can be configured to do the following, Include first day of the interest period and exclude the last of the interest period Exclude the first day of the interest period and include the last of the interest period. Include both first (only value date) and last day of accrual period. Adjust the principal increase and decrease effective dates for interest calculation and accrual calculation purposes. By default the field shall hold null in which case the system shall include first day of the interest period and exclude the last of the interest period. This would be a NOCHANGE field after authorization.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setAdviceReqd

        public void setAdviceReqd(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for AdviceReqd
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Allows user to decide whether they wish to produce any advices associated with this deal. This field allows the user to suppress any advices that would otherwise be produced over the lifetime of the deal. If this field is set to 'NO' then no advices will be produced. If it is set to 'YES' then a subset of the following advices will be produced in association with the deal during its lifetime. 1 Confirmation of Deal 2 Amendment of Deal 3 Cancellation of Deal 4 Charge confirmations Contract confirmation will be produced only on initial input of the contract and cancellation confirmations only when a contract is reversed. Contract amendment confirmations will be produced whenever the contract principal is amended, i.e. when a principal increase or decrease is entered on the deal. It is important to note that this advice is produced when the amendment is made and not on the value date of the actual movement. Therefore, if a second principal movement is entered before the first has reached its value date both movements will appear on the confirmation. Similarly, whenever the maturity date is amended an amendment confirmation will be produced. Charge advices will be produced whenever charges are debited, i.e. on the charge value date. Validation Rules: Input of 'YES' or 'NO' only. (Defaults to 'YES') Only input 'YES' or 'NO' allowed.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        public void setBackForwardKey(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for BackForwardKey
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: BACK.FORWARD.KEY Opens up only if CSN.FREQUENCY is used. The date of application of commission will be based on the value of this field. If the date of application of commission as per the CSN.FREQUENCY is a holiday, this field controls the option to determine the date on which commission is to be collected. When set to 1, Calendar day will be used. When set to 2, Next working day will be used. When set to 3, Previous working day will be used. The default will however be Calendar day. Validation Rules: Valid input 1, 2 or 3.

      • setBaseCcyConv

        public void setBaseCcyConv(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for BaseCcyConv
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This is a User input field, representing the rate at which Facility is to be impacted when the Guarantee currency is different from that of the Facility. Static update of the Facility tables happens at the rate input in this field. The facility limit line is also impacted at this rate. Although the consol entry liquidating the facility happens at this rate, but that of Guarantee happens at Mid Reval Rate. It is important to note that, this rate will be used in the case of reinstatement of limit and facility in case the Facility is of revolving in nature. Validation Rules: Optional input. Default would always be MRR.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setCapitalizeDate

        public void setCapitalizeDate(TField value)
        Set the specified value for CapitalizeDate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: CAPITALIZE.DATE In the case of frequency based scheduling (End type), if the maturity date falls within the running commission schedule, the Deal will be kept "LIVE" past the maturity date till the end of the commission schedule. The commission will be booked at the end of the schedule. This field opens up to enable booking of commission on a day prior to the end date of the running commission schedule, but after the maturity date. Validation Rules: Can be any date past the Maturity date but less than the date in CSN.FREQUENCY.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setCcyMarket

        public void setCcyMarket(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for CcyMarket
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the Currency Market related to this transaction. This field will be applicable where the exchange control authorities have defined different markets for foreign currency dealing. Validation Rules: 1 numeric character Currency Market code (Optional input. Defaults to default currency market for Miscellaneous Deals module on MU.TXN.GRP.CCY.MKT) Must be a valid code on the CURRENCY.MARKET table.         Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the ID of the Consolidation record on the CONSOLIDATE.ASST.LIAB file into which this contract is to be consolidated for financial reporting. This field identifies the CONSOLIDATE.ASST.LIAB record into which the balance details for the contract are consolidated. The criteria for the consolidation of miscellaneous deals are defined on the CONSOLIDATE.CONDS table. This field is maintained by the system during the end of day batch processing. Whenever this field is updated by the system a history record will be written to maintain a full audit trail. Validation Rules: Alphanumeric as specified on the CONSOLIDATE.CONDS file.       • setContractType

        public void setContractType(TField value)
        Set the specified value for ContractType
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Defines the type of Miscellaneous Deal. It defines whether the deal is a Commitment or a Memorandum type deal and whether the deal represents an asset or liability. This field identifies the type of Deal input. It defines whether it is a Commitment or Memorandum deal and whether the figure in the PRINCIPAL.AMOUNT field is an asset or liability. Contract principals will be recorded in the CRF with different asset types according to the CONTRACT.TYPE and contract status as follows:

        TypeForward DealsLive Deals
        CAFWDCONTDBCONTDB
        CLFWDCONTCRCONTCR
        MAFWDMEMODBMEMODB
        MLFWDMEMOCRMEMOCR
        Validation Rules: Once the deal has been authorised the CONTRACT.TYPE cannot be changed. Can only be CA, CL, MA or ML. The CONTRACT.TYPE must be defined on the MD.PARAMETER record for the company concerned.

      • setCsnPaymentType

        public void setCsnPaymentType(TField value)
        Set the specified value for CsnPaymentType
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: At contract level the commission amount payable or receivable can be set to be levied at the beginning (BEGIN) of the commission period or the end (END) of the commission period. The commission period is defined by the start of the contract and the end of the contract with optional interim dates specified by the user. If commission is defined then there must be either a schedule for the start date (for BEGIN contracts) or at maturity (for END contracts). Where it is set to END: Accruals are passed to a P/L category according to the cycling frequency and the customer is debited (or credited according to deal type) at the end of the period. For the bank the effect of the P/L is built up over the life of the contract rather than one lump payment at the end. Where it is set to BEGIN: Accruals are passed to a P/L category according to the cycling frequency and the customer is debited (or credited according to deal type) at the start of the period. This amount is then left in an advance P/L account and then dripped through to the real P/L. This gives the same effect of the P/L build up over the life of the contract as the END method. Validation Rules: BEGIN - payment in advance END - payment in arrears Default is END

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setCsnPaymentType

        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Set the specified value for DealSubType
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field is used to sub divide the CONTRACT.TYPE. This field is used to sub-divide each CONTRACT.TYPE into smaller groups. A Deal Sub Type entered here must have been entered on the MD.PARAMETER record for the company in a position corresponding to the CONTRACT.TYPE entered above. It has no direct bearing on the processing of the deal other than defining the range of allowable categories for the CATEGORY field. It does this through the MD.PARAMETER record. Each Deal Sub Type entered on the MD.PARAMETER is entered with a corresponding range of category codes. This range is used in defining the upper and lower limits for the category code field. Validation Rules: 1 - 5 alphanumeric characters. (Mandatory Input) Once the deal has been authorised this field cannot be changed. Must be present on MD.PARAMETER for the company concerned and must correspond to the CONTRACT.TYPE entered above.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setIncludeProvision

        public void setIncludeProvision(TField value)
        Set the specified value for IncludeProvision
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: INCLUDE.PROVISION Deal level decision to control the impact of Cash Margin on the corresponding limit. If set to YES, the impact on the limit will be reduced to the extent of Cash Margin taken in the Deal, proportionate to the Leader's portion. If set to NO, irrespective of any Cash Margin taken in the Deal, the limit line would reflect the entire amount of the Leader's portion. Will default the value from INCLUDE.PROVISION set in the MD.PARAMETER. Validation Rules: Valid input YES or NO.

        /1235674 - Account Number

      • setInvStatus

        public void setInvStatus(TField value)
        Set the specified value for InvStatus
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Accepts any of PROCESS, EXECUTE or CANCEL. Input allowed only for authorized MD records. The invocation is done two stages. First is the PROCESS stage, where the user can input the invocation details but no accounting entries/limit are raised. When the invocation is in PROCESS stage, the user can either EXECUTE the invocation or CANCEL it. When option EXECUTE is chosen, accounting entries/limit are raised. If CANCEL option is chosen, the invocation fields are cleared. Again no accounting entries/limit are passed. Validation Rules: Invocation related fields open up only if this holds either PROCESS or EXECUTE. The status can only be PROCESS if the previous value is NULL. The status can only be EXECUTE or CANCEL only if the previous value is PROCESS.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setIssueCustomer

        public void setIssueCustomer(TField value)
        Set the specified value for IssueCustomer
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: MD.DEAL allows the participation by other parties in deals, usually on the Issuance of Guarantees for larger amounts. There would typically be a main deal which details the Guarantee issued, the parties who are participating and the commission rates and dates. Secondary deals relating to the Participation taken by the other parties will be recorded in their name with a share of the commission payable to them. In accounting terms this deal is same as a Guarantee Received with the exception that there are commissions to be paid. The Customer entered here is used to identify the client of the main deal. It is not permitted to enter data in this field and the PARTICIPANT or AMT.PARTICIPATE fields at the same time. Validation Rules: Must be a valid CUSTOMER record Cannot be used together with PARTICIPANT or AMT.PARTICIPATE

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setLimitAmount

        public void setLimitAmount(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for LimitAmount
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This is the amount used in the call to limits. The principal amount used for the purposes of limits will be the highest value of the contract either today or in the future taking into account all principal movements. For example consider the following contingent asset contract: 2 CURRENCY USD 4 PRINCIPAL 1,000,000 6 VALUE.DATE 01/01/93 7 MATURITY.DATE 01/04/93 13.1 PRIN.MOVEMENT - 200,000 14.1 MOVEMENT DATE 15/01.93 13.2 PRIN.MOVEMENT 500,000 14.2 MOVEMENT.DATE 01/02/93 13.3 PRIN.MOVEMENT - 100,000 14.3 MOVEMENT.DATE 01/03/93 In this case the principal amount passed to limits would be 1,300,000 as this is the highest value of the principal throughout the contract life. Hence the LIMIT.AMOUNT field would contain 1,300,000. This field will only be updated if LIMIT.UPD.REQD is 'YES'. Validation Rules: Internally generated field. No input allowed.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        public void setLimitReference(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for LimitReference
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Identifies the LIMIT REFERENCE number to be checked for Limit control. If LIMIT.UPD.REQD is 'NO' then this field will be a no- input field and limits will not be called. See help text for field LIMIT UPD REQD as to how that field can be set up. If input is allowed and no input is made in this field the Limits System will provide a default according to the LIMIT.PARAMETER.FILE. It will look for the PRODUCT.NO defined under the MD.DEAL.application. The credit line number generated will be NNNN-01 where NNNN is the ID of the Limit Reference record described above. Validation Rules: 3 to 10 characters for a LIMIT REFERENCE code. Input only allowed if LIMIT.UPD.REQD field is equal to 'YES' otherwise no input. (Optional Input, Default value seel details below) Must be a valid reference on the LIMIT Reference table. If no Limit exists for the counterparty a corresponding error message will be displayed by the system with an override facility. If the transaction amount exceeds the availability amount of the Limit, a corresponding error message will be displayed with an override facility. An override is required if the deal VALUE.DATE is before the limit start date. An override is required if the line expires prior to the deal final maturity date.

        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setLimitUpdReqd

        public void setLimitUpdReqd(TField value)
        Set the specified value for LimitUpdReqd
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Indicates whether limits are to be updated or not. The interface to limits can be controlled both at the contract and parameter level. At the module parameter level fields are provided to control the use of limits with contingent and memorandum contract types. Via these fields the user can specify if the interface to limits is mandatory, optional or not allowed for these products. The fields used on MD.PARAMETER that do this are: CONT.LIMIT.LINK Can be Mandatory, Optional or Noinput. MEMO.LIMIT.LINK Can be Mandatory, Optional or Noinput. CL.LIMIT.LINK Can be Mandatory, Optional or Noinput. ML.LIMIT.LINK Can be Mandatory, Optional or Noinput. If this field is set to YES then limit processing will be perfomed and the limit type define in LIMIT.PARAMETER will be used. If set to No then no processing is done. Validation Rules: Input must either be 'YES' or 'NO' Default of No is used when limits are set to Noinput in MD.PARAMETER

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setLiquidationMode

        public void setLiquidationMode(TField value)
        Set the specified value for LiquidationMode
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field identifies the manner in which overdue payments are handled. The default for all contracts is AUTOMATIC. There are three options available: AUTOMATIC - will liquidate across the charge/commission account on the contract SEMI AUTOMATIC - will liquidate the charge/commission to the account only if sufficient balance is available. Else, PD will be written MANUAL - will create a PD contract irrespective of availability of funds Only the charges and commissions taken in the deal are reckoned for this purpose. If PD product is not defined for the current company, the only allowed value is AUTOMATIC. Prior to inputting MANUAL or SEMI AUTOMATIC, a Parameter for MD has to be defined in PD.PARAMETER

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

      • setMaturityDate

        public void setMaturityDate(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for MaturityDate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field represents either the final maturity date of the deal or the number of days notice before maturity.

        If not defined, maturity date will be calculated from ADVICE.EXPIRY.DATE + EXPIRY.DAYS defined in MD.PARAMETER. Validation Rules:

        Standard date format or 1 - 3 numeric characters.

        An override will be required if the date as defined on the HOLIDAY table is a non working day.

        The date must be greater than the VALUE.DATE defined above.

        An override will be required if the field is changed from a notice to a fixed maturity date and the appropriate number of days' notice has not been given.

        If the MATURITY.DATE has been entered in a Date format then any MOVEMENT.DATEs entered below cannot be after the Maturity Date.

        If the MATURITY.DATE has been entered in a DATE format then any CHARGE.DATEs entered below cannot be after the MATURITY.DATE.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

REQISSUE - Request to issue an undertaking xii.TRANSFER - Transfer of a undertaking Mandatory field for a MT759 message Validation Rules: i.       • setMt759Narrative

        public void setMt759Narrative(java.lang.CharSequence param, int idx)
        Set the specified Mt759Narrative to a specific position in collection.
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Free text fields that allows the user to input the details of the request or the information. This field will be mapped against the tag 45D of a MT759 message. Format : 150*65z ( of 8 sequences) Accept Z (Alphanumeric) characters System auto populates 'tag 27 - Sequence of Total' based on the number of MT759 messages generated. Only upto 8 sequences allowed(i.e. 8/8). This field allows to input a maximum of 1200 lines of 65 characters(Z character set). For each of the 150 lines, T24 generates multiple MT759 messages and a maximum of upto 8/8 sequence of messages can generated. Mandatory field for a MT759 message. Validation Rules: The number of lines in this field cannot exceed 1200.

        Parameters:
        param - the Mt759Narrative to append
        idx - the position in collection
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setOnlineMat

        public void setOnlineMat(TField value)
        Set the specified value for OnlineMat
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Input of YES in this field shall ensure that the maturity of the Guarantee Deal is done Online. This is an input field only if the EVENTS.PROCESSING is set as ONLINE. The Maturity would be treated as TODAY. When set Online maturity, the commission accounting entries, Limit reinstatement, Release of Cash Margin are all done online along with liquidation of the Contract. Where the commission is Begin type and Manual and if the Deal were not in its last schedule, the User needs to delete all the future schedules. The accounting entries would however be passed for the entire schedule amount. Where the commission is End type and Manual and if the Deal were not in its last schedule, the User needs to delete all the future schedules and the CSN.DATE has to be input with Current date. The accounting entries would however be passed only for the amount accrued till date. Thus commission accounting entries passed for the Begin type would always be for the entire current schedule and that of the End type would always be for the Accrued amount. When the Commission is set as a frequency, the system would set the CAPITALIZE.DATE as TODAY and the entries would be passed accordingly. Validation Rules: When set to Online maturity the Deal shall not have any Principal movements scheduled. When set to Online maturity the Deal shall not have any Charges scheduled for a future date. When set to Online maturity the Deal shall not have Invocation set to Process, Execute or Cancel. When set to Online maturity the Deal shall not have its Overdue status relating to PD. Online Maturity shall not take place when the contract is linked to Syndicated Loans. Online Maturity shall not take place where the contract is linked to LC, but Drawings under the same are yet to be done. Online Maturity shall not be permitted for any Forward Deals. This field shall accept either YES or NULL.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setPrincipalAmount

        public void setPrincipalAmount(TField value)
        Set the specified value for PrincipalAmount
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: The principal amount of the deal. This field contains the principal amount of the deal in the currency defined in the CURRENCY field. In order to facilitate the entry of the amount an input feature has been provided which allows for the suppression of trailing zeros. In English language text this is accomplished by using a 'T' to indicate the thousands and an 'M' to indicate the millions. Other languages will require the provision of translation values. e.g. Input Value 1T 1000 2M 2000 000 Validation Rules: 1 - 14 numeric characters plus a decimal point and commas. (Mandatory Input) This field cannot be negative. The decision as to whether the deal represents an asset or liability depends on the value of the CONTRACT.TYPE field entered below. Once the deal has been authorised this field cannot be changed. Any changes to the Principal should be entered using the PRIN.MOVEMENT and MOVEMENT.DATE fields below. This field will then be updated during the end of day of the MOVEMENT.DATE.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setProcessAtSod

        public void setProcessAtSod(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for ProcessAtSod
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field decides whether the commission and charge is to be processed at SOD or EOD of the scheduled date. The value gets defaulted from the parameter table. However, the user can amend the defaulted value. Acceptable values are YES, NO and None. If yes, then the processing will take place during SOD and if no or none, then the processing will take place during EOD of the scheduled date. Validation Rules: Acceptable values are Yes, No and None The value in this field is changeable during the life of the contract.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        DrInvocation Debit AccountUSD 40,000
        CrInvocation Credit AccountUSD 50,000

      • setSplitCommission

        public void setSplitCommission(java.lang.CharSequence value)
        Set the specified value for SplitCommission
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: SPLIT.COMMISSION If this field is set to YES, the calculated commission will be split into two parts, one proportionate to the leader's share in the Deal that is reflected in the P&L and the other will be credited to the Internal account as specified in the MD.PARAMETER (Field PART.CSN.ACC). If set to NO, the entire commission, including that relating to the Participants will move into the P&L. If set to NULL, the flow would be that of NO. Validation Rules: Valid input YES or NO.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setTaxType

        public void setTaxType(TField value)
        Set the specified value for TaxType
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: TAX.TYPE Using this field together with the CONTRACT.GRP, it is possible to determine a particular tax code from the conditions based on: General tax type as defined in TAX.TYPE.CONDITION. Type of customer as defined in CUSTOMER.CHARGE. Type of contract as defined in CONTRACT.GRP field. The value in this field must equate to a record in the TAX.TYPE.CONDITION which contains tax codes related to the customer tax group and contract group. Validation Rules: Optional input, must be present as a record in TAX.TYPE.CONDITION. The actual TAX.TYPE.CONDITION key will be prefixed with '*' character.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setValueDate

        public void setValueDate(TField value)
        Set the specified value for ValueDate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: The value date of the deal. Validation Rules: Standard date format. (Mandatory Input - defaults to current date) An override will be required if the date as defined on the HOLIDAY table is a non working day. Must be prior to the MATURITY.DATE defined below. Once the deal has been authorised this field cannot be changed.

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing
